  "parent": "gl-ES",
  "notes": "A Fala (Xalimego/Fala de Xálima). Galician-Portuguese linguistic island in Cáceres, Extremadura. Three local varieties: Valverdeiru (Valverde del Fresno), Lagarteiro (Eljas), Mañegu (San Martín de Trevejo). ~5,000–10,000 speakers. Preserves medieval Galician-Portuguese features with Leonese/Extremaduran influence (F- → [h] aspiration in some words). Betacism. Nasal vowels. Palatal [ʎ]. ISO 639-3: fax.",
